Our Vegetable Samosa is a delightful concoction of spiced potatoes, peas, and carrots, all encased in a light, flaky pastry. Perfectly fried to a golden crisp, each bite delivers a burst of savory flavors, making it an irresistible starter or a snack to enjoy anytime.

Savor the rich filling of our Chicken Samosa, featuring finely minced chicken, seasoned with an exquisite blend of herbs and spices. Wrapped in a crispy pastry shell, these samosas are a perfect harmony of textures and flavors, ideal for satisfying your hunger with a touch of elegance.

Indulge in the deep, robust flavors of our Lamb Samosa. Packed with juicy, spiced lamb meat, onions, and herbs, each samosa is a pocket of rich, meaty goodness. The crispy outer layer complements the succulent filling, making it a must-try for meat lovers.

Our Vegetable Pakoras are a crunchy, delightful treat. A mixture of fresh vegetables dipped in a chickpea batter and deep-fried to perfection. These fritters are light, flavorful, and an excellent choice for a vegetarian appetizer or a side dish.

Onion Pakora is a popular Indian snack made by coating thinly sliced onions with a spiced batter made from chickpea flour and then deep-frying until crispy and golden brown. The result is a delicious and crunchy snack with a perfect balance of savory and spicy flavors, often served with mint chutney or tamarind chutney on the side.
Paneer pakora are a delicious Indian snack made with paneer, spices & gram flour. These paneer pakora are delicious, flavorful and addictive with all the goodness of Indian cheese in them.

Gobi Pakora is a popular Indian snack made by coating cauliflower florets in a spiced batter of chickpea flour, herbs, and spices before deep-frying until crispy and golden brown. The result is a deliciously crunchy and savory dish with a satisfying kick of heat, perfect as an appetizer or accompaniment to a meal.

Mirchi Pakora is a popular Indian snack made by stuffing long green chilies with a spiced mixture of potatoes, onions, and herbs, before coating them in a batter of chickpea flour and deep-frying until crispy and golden brown. It's a deliciously spicy and crunchy dish that's perfect as a snack or appetizer.

Gobi Manchurian is a popular Indo-Chinese dish made with crispy cauliflower florets coated in a spicy batter and then stir-fried with garlic, ginger, onions, and a tangy sauce made with soy sauce and vinegar. The result is a delicious and flavorful dish with a perfect balance of sweet, sour, and spicy flavors, often served as an appetizer or a side dish.

Experience the bold flavors of our Vegetable Manchurian. Deep-fried vegetable balls are dunked in a tangy, slightly spicy Manchurian sauce, creating a mouth-watering dish that's a staple in Indo-Chinese cuisine. It's a perfect blend of comfort and flavor in every bite.

Our Reshmi Paneer Tikka features succulent cubes of paneer, marinated in a creamy blend of yogurt and spices, then grilled to perfection. Soft and juicy, these paneer tikkas are a heavenly treat for vegetarians and cheese lovers alike.

A unique twist on two classics, our Chicken 65 Manchurian combines the fiery taste of Chicken 65 with the zest of Manchurian sauce. This dish is a fusion of flavors that's spicy, tangy, and absolutely addictive, making it a fantastic choice for those who love a bit of heat.

Our Chicken Tikka Appetizer is marinated in herbs and spices, then grilled until crispy. Served without curry, it's a lighter, flavor-packed start to your meal. Perfect for those who prefer a crisp, savory beginning.

Egg Bhurji is a delicious Indian street food made by hard-boiling eggs, cutting them in half, and coating them in a spiced batter of chickpea flour and deep-frying them until crispy. These egg halves are then served with a tangy and spicy tomato-based sauce and garnished with fresh herbs. It's a perfect snack or appetizer for any occasion.

Fish Pakora is a popular Indian snack made by coating small pieces of fish in a spiced batter of chickpea flour, herbs, and spices before deep-frying until crispy and golden brown. The result is a flavorful and crispy dish with a satisfying kick of heat, perfect as an appetizer or accompaniment to a meal.

Samosa Chaat is a mouth-watering Indian street food made by crushing and layering pieces of crispy samosas with spiced chickpeas, yogurt, tamarind chutney, and green chutney, topped with finely chopped onions, tomatoes, and fresh coriander. The result is a sweet, sour, and savory explosion of flavors and textures, perfect for any food lover.

Aloo Chaat is a popular Indian street food made with boiled and fried potato cubes mixed with spices, tamarind chutney, mint chutney, and yogurt, and then topped with finely chopped onions, tomatoes, and fresh coriander. The result is a delicious and tangy dish with a perfect balance of sweet and sour flavors, perfect for a quick and satisfying snack.

Channa Chaat is a popular Indian street food made with spiced chickpeas, mixed with onions, tomatoes, and potatoes, and then tossed with tamarind chutney, mint chutney, and yogurt. The result is a flavorful and satisfying snack that's perfect for a quick bite on the go, or as an appetizer for any meal.

Aloo Tikki Chaat is a popular Indian street food made with crispy fried potato patties, topped with spiced chickpeas, tamarind chutney, mint chutney, and yogurt, and then garnished with finely chopped onions, tomatoes, and fresh coriander. The result is a delicious and satisfying snack with a perfect balance of flavors and textures.

Papadi Chaat is a popular Indian street food made with crispy deep-fried flour crisps called 'papadis,' topped with spiced chickpeas, potatoes, and onions, and then drizzled with tamarind chutney, mint chutney, and yogurt. The result is a tangy and savory snack with a perfect balance of textures and flavors, and a must-try for any street food lover.

Pani Puri, also known as Gol Guppa, is a popular Indian street food consisting of small, crispy, hollow balls filled with spiced potatoes, chickpeas, and tamarind chutney, and then filled with a spicy and tangy mint water called 'pani'. The result is a burst of flavors and textures in every bite, and a must-try for any street food enthusiast.

Dhai Bhalla is a popular Indian snack made with deep-fried lentil dumplings that are soaked in water to make them soft, and then topped with yogurt, tamarind chutney, and a mix of spices. The result is a tangy, spicy, and creamy dish with a perfect balance of flavors and textures, and a favorite of many Indian food lovers.

Enjoy the simplicity of our Freshly Tossed Green Salad, a vibrant mix of fresh greens and garden vegetables, lightly dressed to enhance their natural flavors. Its the perfect refreshing complement to any meal.

Our Cucumber Salad offers a crisp and refreshing bite, featuring thinly sliced cucumbers and a hint of herbs, all tossed in a light vinaigrette. It's a cool, soothing side dish ideal for balancing spicier flavors.

Papadum is a thin, crisp, and disc-shaped flatbread that is a popular snack and side dish in Indian cuisine. It is made with a combination of lentil or chickpea flour, spices, and sometimes rice flour, which is then rolled into a thin dough and sun-dried or roasted until crispy. Papadum is often served as an appetizer or with main courses such as curries, biryanis, and kebabs.
A spicy salad that consists of onions topped with chilli poweder, fresh lettuce and spinach, and topped freshly squeezed lime.

Fresh Plain Dhai, also known as yogurt or curd, is a staple ingredient in Indian cuisine. It is made by fermenting milk with lactic acid bacteria, resulting in a tangy and creamy texture. Fresh Plain Dhai is often served as a cooling accompaniment to spicy dishes, used as a marinade, or added to various recipes as a souring agent.

Boondi Rayta is a popular yogurt-based condiment in Indian cuisine. It is made by mixing fresh plain dhai with boondi (tiny fried chickpea flour balls) and flavored with spices such as cumin, coriander, and chaat masala. Boondi Rayta is often served as a cooling accompaniment to spicy dishes, biryanis, and kebabs.

Cool down with our Cucumber Raita, a creamy yogurt-based condiment dotted with grated cucumber and seasoned with a dash of spices. This soothing dish is excellent for tempering the heat and adding a creamy texture to your meal.

Savor the flavors of our Tandoori Leg Quarter, expertly marinated in a blend of traditional spices and slow-cooked to perfection in a clay oven. Each succulent piece is served with a side of aromatic rice and crispy masala-fried potato slices, combining rich flavors and textures for a delightful meal.

Our Whole Tandoori Chicken is marinated in a rich blend of spices and yogurt, then slow-roasted in a traditional tandoor oven. The result is succulent, smoky, and perfectly charred chicken that's a feast for the senses.

Savor the rich flavors of our Half-Tandoori Chicken, expertly marinated and roasted to achieve a delightful smoky crispness. Perfect for those who want the full tandoori experience on a smaller scale.

Experience the juicy delight of our Chicken Seekh Kabab, where minced chicken is seasoned with a medley of spices, molded onto skewers, and grilled to perfection. Each bite is tender, flavorful, and irresistibly aromatic.

Our Lamb Seekh Kabab features finely ground lamb, infused with herbs and spices, then grilled on skewers to create a savory, melt-in-your-mouth experience. It's a rich and hearty choice for kabab lovers.

Lamb Chops are a delicious and popular appetizer or main course in Indian cuisine. The lamb chops are marinated in a mixture of yogurt and Indian spices, including garam masala, cumin, coriander, ginger, and garlic, and then grilled or broiled until tender and flavorful. Lamb Chops are often served with mint chutney and naan bread.

Indulge in our Tandoori Prawn, where large, succulent prawns are marinated in a special blend of spices and grilled until perfectly charred. These prawns are a luxurious addition to any meal, offering a smoky, spicy kick.

Our Sizzling Mixed Grill is a carnivore's dream, featuring an assortment of tandoori specialties including chicken, lamb, and prawns. Served hot and sizzling, this platter is perfect for sharing and sampling a variety of grilled delights.

Grilled fish is typically marinated in a blend of Indian spices such as cumin, coriander, turmeric, and chili powder, as well as lemon or lime juice and oil. The fish can be served as a whole or in fillets and is usually grilled in a tandoor oven. It is often garnished with fresh herbs and served with a side of rice.

A beloved classic, our Chicken Tikka Masala features grilled chicken tikka smothered in a creamy, spiced tomato sauce. This dish combines rich flavors with a hint of sweetness, making it a favorite for all palates.

Our Butter Chicken is a velvety delight, with tender chicken pieces cooked in a smooth, buttery tomato sauce with a touch of cream. It's mild yet flavorful, perfect for those who enjoy a less spicy taste.
For those who dare, our Chicken Vindaloo Gourmet offers a fiery blend of spices cooked with chicken in a tangy vinegar-based sauce. This dish is bold and intense, designed to satisfy lovers of heat.
Chicken Madras is a hot, fragrant dish cooked with mustard seeds, curry leaves, and coconut. Its depth of flavor and spicy kick make it a compelling choice for adventurous eaters.
Our Chicken Korma Kashmiri is a luxurious dish made with boneless chicken cooked in a creamy, nutty sauce with a hint of saffron. It's mildly spiced, making it a sumptuous and soothing dish.
Chicken Saag combines tender chicken pieces with a flavorful spinach sauce, seasoned with a mix of herbs and spices. This hearty and nutritious dish is both comforting and satisfying.
Made from delicious chicken chunks Kebabs with a Curry made of cream, ground cashews, and almonds.
Chili Chicken is a must-try for spice enthusiasts, featuring chicken pieces tossed in a spicy chili sauce with bell peppers and onions. This Indo-Chinese fusion is vibrant and exciting on the palate.
Our Chicken Karahi is a robust dish cooked in a thick tomato-based sauce with fresh herbs and spices, served directly in the cooking pot for added authenticity and flavor.
Made by cooking chicken with pickling spices. 'Achar' is a Punjabi term that means pickeled.

Enjoy the pure comfort of our Chicken Curry, boneless chicken cooked in a traditional curry sauce. This dish is rich in flavors, with a perfect balance of spices that envelop the tender chicken pieces.

Our Goat Curry is a robust, deeply flavorful dish, featuring tender goat meat slow-cooked in a rich blend of spices and a hearty sauce. This traditional recipe delivers a taste of authentic Indian cuisine, perfect for those who appreciate a strong, meaty flavor.

Indulge in the aromatic spices of our Goat Masala (Gosht Masala), where goat pieces are simmered in a thick, spicy tomato and onion sauce. This dish is a celebration of flavors, offering a satisfying complexity that spice lovers will adore.
Goat Madras is a fairly hot curry sauce that goast chunks of goat in red color and with heavy use of chili powder.

For those who crave heat, our Goat Vindaloo is a fiery delight. Prepared with chunks of goat meat marinated in vinegar and spices, then cooked with hot chili peppers, this dish is intensely spicy and incredibly flavorful.

Experience the luxurious side of goat dishes with our Goat Korma Kashmiri. This mild curry is made with tender goat meat cooked in a creamy, nutty sauce enriched with delicate spices and a hint of saffron. It's a wonderfully rich dish that perfectly balances flavor and creaminess.

Our Lamb Curry is a savory delight, featuring tender pieces of lamb slow-cooked in a rich, aromatic curry sauce. This dish highlights the natural flavors of the meat enhanced by a carefully curated blend of spices, making it a hearty and comforting choice.
This is a classic indian curry recipe thats been given an extra depth of flavour with the lamb and tickles the taste buds with a kick of chilli heat.

Lamb Vindaloo is an adventurous choice for those who love their meals with a kick. This dish combines tender lamb with a potent mix of vinegar, hot chili, and spices, creating a deep, fiery flavor that's both bold and invigorating.

Indulge in the exquisite Lamb Korma Kashmiri, where succulent lamb pieces are bathed in a creamy, luxurious sauce made with cashews, almonds, and a touch of saffron. This rich dish is mild yet deeply flavorful, offering a sublime culinary experience.

Our Lamb Rogan Josh is a classic Kashmiri dish known for its vibrant red color and complex flavors. Cooked with a variety of spices, yogurt, and garlic, this dish features succulent lamb pieces that are tender and richly coated in a savory, aromatic sauce.

Paneer Tikka Masala features grilled paneer (cheese) cubes in a creamy, spiced tomato sauce. This dish is a delightful blend of rich flavors and textures, perfect for those who enjoy a hearty vegetarian option.
Enjoy marinated, grilled cauliflower florets bathed in a creamy, spiced tomato sauce. This smoky and silky vegetarian dish is a comforting, hearty choice.
Shahi Paneer is a succulent dish made with soft, pillowy paneer floating in a creamy gravy of yogurt and nuts.
Paneer Makhani, also known as Butter Paneer, combines soft paneer in a smooth, buttery gravy enriched with cream. Its mild flavor and luxurious texture make it a comforting choice for all ages.
Malai Kofta offers melt-in-your-mouth vegetable and cheese balls served in a creamy, mild curry sauce. This dish is a festive treat, perfect for special occasions or indulgent dinners.
a delicious combination of soft paneer and healthy green peas with cashews made in a mild spicy tomato based gravy.
Kadhai Paneer features paneer and bell peppers tossed in a thick, spicy tomato-based sauce. Cooked in a traditional kadhai (wok), this dish offers a burst of fresh flavors and a delightful aroma.

Saag-Palak Paneer combines creamy paneer with a delicious mixture of spinach and mustard greens. Seasoned with mild spices, it's both nutritious and flavorful, making it a popular choice for health-conscious diners.
Baingan Bharta is a smoky, mashed eggplant dish cooked with onions, tomatoes, and a variety of spices. Its a flavorful, earthy dish that pairs wonderfully with flatbreads or rice.
Aloo Gobi Masala features potatoes and cauliflower cooked in a spicy masala sauce. This classic dish is loved for its bold flavors and satisfying texture, making it a staple in vegetarian cuisine.

Shahai Matar Paneer offers a luxurious version of the classic peas and paneer dish, cooked in a rich, creamy sauce. It's a perfect blend of sweet peas and soft paneer, making it a comforting and hearty choice.

Navratan Korma is a creamy and colorful dish with nine different vegetables and fruits in a mild, nutty gravy. It's a royal dish that celebrates the diversity of flavors and textures in Indian cuisine.
Chana Masala, known in Amritsar as Chole, features tangy, spiced chickpeas that are a staple in North Indian cuisine. Its robust and flavorful, perfect for pairing with fluffy bhature or rice.
Daal Makhani is a rich, creamy dish made with black lentils and kidney beans, slow-cooked with butter and cream. Its a luxurious staple that's both nourishing and comforting.
Daal Fry is a popular Indian lentil dish, cooked with onions, tomatoes, and tempered with spices. Its light yet flavorful, making it an excellent side dish that complements any main course.
Bhindi Masala is a healthy dish made with okra, whole and ground spices, onions and tomatoes.
Our Boiled Rice is a simple yet perfect staple, featuring fluffy, aromatic Basmati rice. It's versatile and can be paired with any of our curries or grilled dishes to enhance your meal.
Zeera Rice is delicately flavored with cumin seeds, giving it a nutty aroma and taste. This fragrant Basmati rice dish is a subtle yet flavorful accompaniment to any of our savory main courses.
Peas Pulao is a colorful Basmati rice dish dotted with bright green peas, lightly seasoned to perfection. Its a delightful and aromatic side that pairs wonderfully with any of our rich, spicy dishes.

Our Vegetable Fried Rice turns simple Basmati rice into a vibrant and savory feast with the addition of fresh, crunchy vegetables. Its a flavorful and hearty dish that can stand alone or complement any entre.

Egg & Vegetable Fried Rice combines fluffy Basmati rice with eggs and mixed vegetables, stir-fried to create a satisfying and nutritious dish. It's perfect for those seeking a protein-rich rice option.
Chicken & Vegetable Fried Rice is a hearty meal, with tender chicken pieces and mixed vegetables stir-fried with Basmati rice. This dish is a flavorful, fulfilling choice for chicken lovers.
Our Shrimp & Vegetable Fried Rice features succulent shrimp and mixed vegetables sauted with Basmati rice. Its a seafood delight that offers both freshness and flavor in every bite.
Vegetable Biryani is a rich and aromatic Basmati rice dish cooked with a medley of fresh vegetables and traditional spices. This vibrant and flavorful biryani is a vegetarian feast all on its own.

Chicken Biryani is a beloved Indian classic, where marinated chicken pieces are layered with spiced Basmati rice and slow-cooked to perfection. Its aromatic, flavorful, and a true celebration of flavors.

Our Lamb Biryani features tender pieces of lamb embedded in fragrant Basmati rice, cooked with a blend of exotic spices. This dish is rich, hearty, and packed with robust flavors, ideal for any lamb enthusiast.

Goat Biryani is a luxurious dish where succulent goat meat is slow-cooked with Basmati rice and a complex blend of spices. Its a bold and flavorful choice that's both traditional and deeply satisfying.
Tandoori Roti refers to a bread baked in a clay oven called a tandoor.
A double-folded Roti that is flattened with a roller and cooked on a flat hot iron.
A double-folded Roti that is filled with either herbs or vegetables and flattened, then cooked on a flat hot iron.

Our Butter Naan is a soft, fluffy flatbread made from finely milled flour and baked in a tandoor. Brushed with butter, it has a slight sweetness that complements any of our savory dishes. Its perfect for scooping up curries or enjoying as a delicious wrap.
Aloo (Potato) Naan is filled with mashed potatos mixed with masalas and spices.

Onion Naan is a flavorful twist on the traditional flatbread, infused with finely chopped onions and a hint of cilantro. Baked until golden and crispy, it offers a savory crunch that enhances the flavors of any meal. Ideal for those who love a little extra texture and taste in their bread.
Garlic Naan is topped with minced garlic, chopped onions, cilantro, and a light masala.
Keema (minced meat) Naan is filled with minced meat, onions, spices, and cooked in a tandoor.
A naan with a spicy kick! It's topped with spicy masalas right on the top layer.
Kashmiri Naan is one of the sweetest and flakiest naan varieties originated from Kashmiri cuisine. It's stuffed with cherry and cashew paste or mixture and some nuts and dry fruits toppings.
An aromatic, comforting curry made in a pressure cooker. In India, this curry is normally made with other meats but this one is a special made with Jump Prawns/Shrimp.
Shrimp Masala is made with shrimps cooked in a semi-dry gravy of onions and tomatoes, seasoned with curry leaves, mustard seeds, and a blend of spices.

Savor succulent shrimp simmered in a luxurious sauce made from tomatoes, cream, and a blend of traditional spices like garam masala and fenugreek. This creamy, buttery dish is a delightful seafood adaptation of the classic Indian favorite, perfect for indulging your taste buds.
Spicy Fish Masala is prepared with wild sole cooked in tomatoes and Indian spices.
Fish tikka masala is an Indian dish made by simmering grilled fish in a spicy masala. It is a variation of the most popular chicken tikka masala.
A delicious snack and staple of Punjabi cuisine. A hot 'puri' (a deep fried Chapati Roti) that's served with 'Chana', a yellow curry made with white chick-peas.
Channa is the same Channa Masala, which is a chick pea curry and it's paired with 2 deep fried chapati rotis.
Sweet Lassi is a cool creamy yogurt drink made by blending various spices along with water and yogurt.
This Lassi is perfect to accompany salt meals!
Enjoy a classic refreshment with our Sweetened Iced Tea. Perfectly brewed and chilled, with just the right amount of sweetness to quench your thirst on a hot day.
Our Un-sweetened Iced Tea offers a crisp and invigorating taste. Its freshly brewed and served chilled, providing a pure, refreshing experience without the sweetness.
Our Hot Coffee is rich and aromatic, made from freshly ground beans that provide a robust flavor. It's the perfect pick-me-up at any time of the day.
Enjoy the bold, refreshing flavor of Pepsi, a classic cola that pairs perfectly with any dish on our menu.
Savor the timeless taste of Coca-Cola, an ideal complement to your meal with its distinctive, crisp flavor.

Indulge in the unique blend of 23 flavors with Dr. Pepper, a satisfying treat with a bold, distinctive taste.

Coke Zero gives you all the classic Coca-Cola flavor without the calories, making it a perfect choice for calorie-conscious guests.
Sprite is a light, crisp beverage with a lemon-lime twist that refreshes and invigorates.
Crisp and refreshing, Sprite in a classic glass bottle offers a bright burst of lemon-lime flavor, perfect for quenching thirst.
Brighten your meal with Sunkist, a delightful orange soda that offers a sweet, fruity burst of flavor.
Diet Coke delivers the same crisp taste as Coca-Cola but with no calories, ideal for those who prefer a lighter soda option.
Enjoy the pure taste of apples with Minute Maid Apple Juice, offering a sweet and refreshing flavor in every sip.

Experience the exotic flavor of Jumex Guava Nectar, a deliciously sweet and aromatic beverage made from fresh guavas.
Dive into the unique and tangy flavor of Jarritos Tamarind, a traditional Mexican soda that's both bold and refreshing.
Refresh with Jarritos Mandarin, a bright and bubbly soda bursting with sweet citrus flavor, straight from Mexico.

This almonds and cashew rich soft and savory sooji halwa prepared without milk is a welcome treat for taste buds.

Our Carrot Halwa is a rich, pudding-like dessert made from grated carrots cooked in milk, sugar, and ghee, then garnished with nuts. It's warm, sweet, and perfectly spiced, offering a comforting end to any meal.
Ras Malai features soft, cheese-based balls soaked in creamy, cardamom-flavored milk syrup. This delicate and luscious dessert is a soothing treat, loved for its light and airy texture.
Gulab Jamun are deep-fried dough balls, luxuriously soaked in a sweet, saffron-infused syrup. This popular dessert is soft, juicy, and melts in your mouth, providing a warm burst of sweet flavor.

Jalebi is a traditional Indian sweet made from fermented batter spiraled into hot oil and then soaked in syrup. These bright orange treats are crisp, sticky, and absolutely addictive, with a delightful crunch.

Kheer, a classic Indian rice pudding, combines rice, milk, and sugar, simmered to creamy perfection and flavored with cardamom, raisins, and nuts. It's a gentle, soothing dessert, perfect for rounding off a spicy meal.
Indulge in these sweet, round treats made from flour, ghee, and sugar, enhanced with cardamom and nuts. Perfect for celebrations or a delightful dessert.

Mini egg rolls filled with a mixture of vegetables and chicken, all wrapped in a crispy shell. They're bite-sized and perfect for little hands, making them a fun and tasty treat.
Quick, flavorful, and loved by children, our Maggie Noodles are tossed in a savory sauce with just the right amount of seasoning. They offer a simple yet satisfying meal that kids crave.

menu.description: The closest you can get to the Gyu-Kaku yakiniku experience without grilling the meat yourself. Customize your meal! Select two proteins as single or double portions, two marinades, and rice portion. Includes Miso Soup, White Rice, and a Set Salad.

The closest you can get to the Gyu-Kaku yakiniku experience without grilling the meat yourself. Customize your meal! Select three proteins as single or double portions, three marinades, and rice portion. Includes Miso Soup, White Rice, and a Set Salad.

Crunchy Garlic Shrimp atop thick Japanese noodles stir-fried with sliced garlic, crunchy chili garlic oil, butter, and soy sauce. Topped with diced red bell peppers, chopped green onions, and sesame seeds. Mildly spicy.
Thick Japanese noodles stir-fried with chicken, sliced garlic, butter, and soy sauce. Topped with diced red bell peppers, chopped green onions, and sesame seeds.
Our signature thin-sliced Sukiyaki-marinated beef stir-fried with white rice, egg yolk, mushrooms, and sliced onions. Topped with diced red bell peppers, chopped green onions, and sesame seeds.

Our beloved Sukiyaki Bibimbap goes BEYOND. 100% plant-based Beyond Beef is marinated in our secret Sukiyaki sauce and stir fried with mushrooms, diced red bell peppers, and sliced white onions. Served over rice. Topped with chopped green onions and sesame seeds. Also contains butter and sesame oil. Picture for visualization purposes only. Beyond Bibimbap will arrive pre-mixed.
Japanese Fried Chicken Karaage on a bed of white rice and shredded cabbage. Topped with Japanese Chili Mayo and chopped green onions.

Our Garlic Fried Rice features white rice stir-fried with egg yolk, sliced onions, sliced garlic. Seasoned with a combination of our Shio Soy Sauce, butter, sesame oil, and black pepper. Topped with chopped green onions and fried garlic chips.
Premium roast beef on a bed of mixed greens and steamed rice. Topped with white and green onions, Signature soy-based barbecue sauce, and kuki wasabi.
Beef rib meat and rice dowsed in our signature Umakara Sauce and mixed with an assortment of bell pepper, shishito pepper, and corn, then garnished with sesame, green onions, and chili flakes.
Thin-sliced Yakishabu beef marinated in our sweet & spicy Umakara sauce with sliced onions on a bed of white rice and shredded cabbage. Topped with chopped green onions and sesame seeds.

Gyu-Kaku original recipe: Japanese BBQ meets Ramen! Rich kalbi beef soup and medium thickness ramen noodles topped with thin-sliced beef, boiled egg, green onions, spinach, daikon radish, and sesame seeds. Ramen noodles and hot soup are packaged separately to maintain their maximum deliciousness. Please reheat soup in the microwave (if necessary) and pour over noodles.

Our Tonkotsu pork bone ramen comes with chunky, fatty braised pork belly Kakuni chashu and is topped with hard-boiled egg, chopped green onions, diced red bell peppers, and sesame seeds. Ramen noodles and hot soup are packaged separately to maintain their maximum deliciousness. Please reheat soup in the microwave (if necessary) and pour over noodles.

Beef and shio-based soup with medium-thick ramen noodles and thick braised pork belly Kakuni chashu. Toppings also include boiled egg, green onion, and sesame seeds. Ramen noodles and hot soup are packaged separately to maintain their maximum deliciousness. Please reheat soup in the microwave (if necessary) and pour over noodles.

We have put together some of our fan favorites to create a well-balance meal that feeds four. Substitutions respectfully declined. Includes: 1x Gyu-Combo with 7 oz Yaki-shabu Beef in Miso, 1x Gyu-Combo with 7 oz Toro Beef in Sweet Soy Tare, 1x Beef Sukiyaki Fried Rice, 1x Garlic Shoyu Chicken Noodles, 1x Black Pepper Wings, 1x Fried Pork Gyoza, 1x Gyu-Kaku Salad, 1x Edamame, and 1x Napa Kimchi

A TRIPLE SERVING of our Crowd Favorite: Sukiyaki Fried Rice with Beef. Serves 3-5 people. Our signature thin-sliced Sukiyaki-marinated beef stir-fried with white rice, egg yolk, mushrooms, and sliced onions. Topped with diced red bell peppers, chopped green Onions, and sesame seeds.

A TRIPLE SERVING of our Crowd Favorite: Mega Garlic Noodles with Chicken. Serves 3-5 people. Thick Japanese noodles stir-fried with chicken, sliced garlic, butter, and soy sauce. Topped with diced red bell peppers, chopped green onions, and sesame seeds.

Stir fried stick rice noodles with authentic sauce from palm sugar and tamarind paste, including egg, bean sprouts, chives.

Stir fried soy sauce noodles, is an extremely popular Thai street food meal and one of the most popular noodles dishes in Thai restaurants. A signature flavor in Pad See Ew is the caramelization of the noodles.

There is another noodle dish beloved by Thai people - yet very few Thai restaurants overseas offer it. It's a dish that showed up regularly on dinner table in Thailand, and one that deserves a place on yours! Either crispy egg noodles or flat fresh rice noodles.

Kee Mao noodle or drunken noodles is stir fried rice noodles with holy basil and lots of chilies. It's a cult-favorite Thai street food. The combination of chewy fresh rice noodles, egg, sweet onion, bell pepper, the epic savory sauce, and the fragrant holy basil.

One of the most iconic dishes in Thailand is boat noodles or guay tiew ruea. It's so named because originally, they were actually sold from boats along Bangkok's canals; though nowadays most vendors have moved on land, and you can find them all over.

'Mama' is Thailand's favorite brand of instant noodles, and we love it so much we use it in all sorts of recipes. These Mama noodles have a very unique texture and flavor which work well in so many dishes. The flavor of the eggs once they've been broken into the soup.

Pad Woon Sen or glass noodle stir fry is a staple dish in most Thai homes. Chewy glass noodles are stir fried with vegetables, eggs and any meat of your choice. It's a great dish if you're inexperienced with stir frying noodles as glass noodles are quick and easy.

Tom Yum is a type of Thai hot and sour soup where the iconic flavors come from 3 herbs: lemongrass, galangal, and makrut (kaffir) lime leaves. You can call these herbs the 'Tom Yum trinity.' Thai people usually eat Tom Yum soup with rice, but you can also have it with noodles.

Noodle soup or Kuay Teaw Nam, is one of the poster children of Thai street food. No matter where you are in the country, you can find a shop selling some type of noodle soup near you. There are many, many different kinds of noodle soups in Thailand.

Kuay Teaw Kua is sort of the sister of the more popular Pad See Ew. It uses the same chewy fresh rice noodles that wok-fried until toasty but usually comes with chicken (that's the gai in the name) but you can choose any kind of your favorite meat.

Khao Soi is a northern Thai noodle soup that uses wheat-based egg noodles and is served in a coconut milk curry broth. It's typically made with chicken or beef, and the bowl is topped with crispy deep fried noodles. Because Northern Thailand is such a melting pot of cultures.

This fried rice recipe that looks too simple to be anything special, but its flavor will surprise you! This is a standard fried rice formula in Thailand, and few things are more satisfying to you than a plate of Thai fried rice with a squeeze of lime.

menu.item_name: FR2. Thai Fried Rice with Nam
menu.description: This Thai yummy fried rice with fermented pork is very popular throughout Thailand.

This fried rice features not one, not two, but three different types of chilies, combined with the fragrance of Thai basil to tie it all together! And no, it doesn't make this dish overwhelmingly spicy, and you can indeed customize the heat level.

This is arguably the most popular type of fried rice in Thailand - so much so that there are restaurants in Thailand specializing only in this one dish. It's certainly Thai favorite fried rice, especially for kids growing up in Thailand. Simple, unfussy.

Many people seem surprised that pineapple fried rice is a real Thai dish, not just a tourist-trap meal in beach-side resorts! It's a delicious and quick dish that only takes a few minutes on the stove. But with so many components, it can be a bit tricky.

This fried rice, though named 'American', is a uniquely Thai experience. It contains ingredients that we associate with American food: ketchup, sunny side up egg, and fried chicken drumsticks. In Thailand, this is one of the most popular dishes among children.

menu.item_name: E10. Pad Ka-Prao Kai Yeo Ma

menu.description: Panang curry is one of the most popular curries in Thailand and overseas alike. It's also gluten-free and can be made vegan. This Panang curry recipe can be made with pork, which is the most popular protein in Thailand, but you can substitute any kind.

Pad Ped Nor Mai is a traditional Thai dish featuring bamboo shoots stir-fried with spices and often chicken or shrimp with Thai eggplants and basil. Its a staple in Thai cuisine, beloved for its spicy, savory flavors and crisp texture of bamboo.

Kang Dang or Thai red curry is a spicy and aromatic blend of red curry paste, coconut milk, Thai eggplants, bamboo shoot, basil and a protein like chicken or pork, or vegetables. Its a blend of sweet, salty, spicy, and umami, combined into one.

Kang Keaw Wan or green curry is a Thai dish made with Thai eggplants, bamboo shoot, basil, green curry paste, coconut milk, and an optional protein. The flavor balances spicy, creamy, and slightly sweet, often paired with jasmine rice or rice vermicelli.

Thai yellow curry or Kang Karee is a classic Thai dish and popular amongst Thais and foreigners alike. It's rich with coconut milk, full of aromatic spices, and it's a mildly spiced curry. The yellow color comes from turmeric, which is added fresh to the curry paste.

Kang Massaman is usually prepared with chicken or beef instead of pork because of its Muslim origin. Its a signature dish of Southern Thai cuisine and a perfect example of how cultural fusion can create unique dishes. It began with Muslim traders in the region.
Kang Dang Supparos or Thai pineapple red curry is perfect for all pineapple lovers out there! The pineapple adds a naturally sweet and refreshing flavor thats simply irresistible.

Mixed Vegetable Stir Fried or Pad Pak Ruam Mit is a classic vegetarian Thai stir-fry dish featuring seasonal or mixed vegetables. Beloved for its simplicity and deliciously savory stir-fry sauce, this popular vegetarian option is often enjoyed as a side dish or main.

You might be familiar with a Chinese restaurant dish with long stems of steamed Gai Lan (aka Chinese broccoli) on a plate with oyster sauce drizzled on top, and this is a similar idea except BETTER! It's all cut up, so you don't have to try to eat whole stems.

Thai omelet or Kai Jeaw is such easy comfort food and help to cool down while you are having other spicy dishes. This beaten egg recipe is full of flavor, with umami-rich fish sauce, the savory depth of oyster sauce and your choice of ground pork, crab, or shrimp.
This dish really represents taste of Thai cuisine by red curry coconut milk and the aroma from kaffir lime leaf.
This crispy fish has a sweet, tangy and spicy sauce made with lots of chili and garlic. It is a very popular dish in Thailand.

menu.description: Immerse yourself in a symphony of flavors with the vibrant combination of fresh watermelon, pineapple, & mango, harmoniously blended with the invigorating essence of cold-brewed jasmine green tea. Indulge in the tropical paradise captured in every sip.

The refreshing fusion of black tea infused with the vibrant flavors of zesty oranges, juicy peaches, and fragrant lemongrass-a tantalizing blend that awakens your senses with every sip. Experience the perfect harmony of tea and fruits in a single, invigorating beverage.
Immerse yourself in the luscious combination of fresh mangoes and the fragrant essence of cold brew jasmine tea. Sip your way to pure, fruity bliss.
Experience the essence of summer with our Peach Jasmine Cold Brew Teaa delightful fusion of juicy peach and refreshing jasmine tea. Pure bliss in a sip!
Indulge in the yumminess of our strawberry-infused cold brew jasmine tea, a blissful fusion of fruity sweetness and floral notes.
Awaken your senses with our vibrant infusion of fresh pineapple, mango, and orange, blended harmoniously with the smoothness of cold-brew jasmine tea. A tropical paradise in every sip!
A great combination of fresh oranges with Cold brew green tea! This refreshing drink infused with the tangy essence of fresh oranges. A vibrant delight!
Crafted from real strawberries and fizzy soda, this vibrant blend delivers a burst of fruity goodness in every sip. Pure delight in a glass!
This refreshing orange and lemonade with all fresh ingredients is just what you need on a hot day, or anytime you feel like a cool and delicious drink!
Quench your thirst with our Mango Lemonade! Made from fresh mango and soda, this refreshing blend offers a burst of tropical sweetness in every sip.
This blend of sweetened organic pure matcha green tea, milk and topped off with sweetened whipped cream-inspires a delicious boost and good green vibes.
Strong, frozen, and creamy, this refreshing concoction offers an invigorating caffeine kick wrapped in a velvety texture. Experience a frosty coffee experience like never before!

Indulge in the perfect harmony of sweetness and creaminess, combined with a delightful espresso twist and topped with luscious whipped cream. This divine concoction will take your taste buds on a blissful journey of flavors. Treat yourself to a moment of pure delight!

A bold and creamy delight, it features a rich coffee base adorned with a luscious macchiato foam. Topped off with a tantalizing touch of cinnamon, this extraordinary blend promises a delightful and unforgettable coffee experience that will leave you craving for more

A delightful blend of velvety coffee and luscious hazelnut flavors, this icy treat is the perfect pick-me-up on a warm day. Sip and savor the irresistible harmony of coffee and hazelnut in every frosty sip

Made with rich chocolate and real Oreo cookies, this divine blend is a tantalizing treat for your taste buds. Dive into the lusciousness of every sip and relish the perfect harmony of Vanilla and cookie goodness. It's a match made in dessert heaven!
This delightful blend combines the smoothness of vanilla with the invigorating kick of coffee, creating a heavenly treat to satisfy your cravings. A taste of pure bliss awaits with every sip!
Indulge in the rich, smooth flavor and the refreshing chill that will invigorate your senses. A heavenly blend that promises to satisfy your coffee cravings in the most delightful way!

A delightful concoction of sweetness and creaminess, perfectly balanced with a shot of espresso and a hint of cinnamon. Indulge in this heavenly blend, where rich flavors unite to create a satisfyingly refreshing treat. Sip and savor the magic in every icy-cold, comforting sip.

menu.item_name: VietNamese Coffee (Brown Coffee) [Ca Phe Sua Da]
menu.description: Vietnamese coffee style. A powerhouse of flavor with super-strong espresso shots and creamy condensed milk. Experience the perfect balance of boldness and sweetness in every refreshing sip. A true coffee lover's delight!

Sea Salt Vietnamese Coffee is a high quality blend of strong coffee, with a delightful balance of sweetness and creaminess. Its unique twist lies in the subtle touch of saltiness, creating a harmonious and enticing flavor combination
Experience a tropical awakening with our Coconut Coffee! A creamy blend of coconut frappe and energizing espresso, this tasty concoction will wake you up and whisk you away to paradise.

Savor the bold energy of espresso infused with creamy textures. Topped with freshly torched crme brle, it's the perfect blend of rich flavors and invigorating caffeine. Experience coffee like never before with our Torched Crme Brle Latte!
